ACTIVITY_TYPE: Qualifier for the value of EC50
EC50_MICROM: Effective concentration of half maximal event count as estimated by curve fit
EC50_95CI_LOW: Lower 95% confidence interval boundary for the EC50 curve fit estimate
EC50_95CI_HIGH: Upper 95% confidence interval boundary for the EC50 curve fit estimate
BOTTOM: Response value at the bottom plateau
TOP: Response value at the top plateau
HILLSLOPE: Hill slope estimate for the fitted dose response curve
STD_BOTTOM: Standard error for the response value at the bottom plateau
STD_TOP: Standard error for the response value at the top plateau
STD_LOGEC50: Standard error for the Log EC50 value
STD_HILLSLOPE: Standard error for the HILL SLOPE
RSQR: Correlation coefficient for the fitted dose response curve
N_POINTS: Number of data points for each dose response curve
%Response_0.01uM: Percent Response measured with 0.01 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_0.02uM: Percent Response measured with 0.02 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_0.05uM: Percent Response measured with 0.05 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_0.14uM: Percent Response measured with 0.14 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_0.41uM: Percent Response measured with 0.41 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_1.23uM: Percent Response measured with 1.23 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_3.72uM: Percent Response measured with 3.72 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_11.22uM: Percent Response measured with 11.22 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
%Response_33.11uM: Percent Response measured with 33.11 micromolar concentration of test compound first repetition
